sailpoint.object

Class AuditEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.tools.xml.AbstractXmlObject
      • sailpoint.object.SailPointObject
        • sailpoint.object.AuditEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, sailpoint.tools.xml.PersistentXmlObject, sailpoint.tools.xml.XMLReferenceTarget

    public class AuditEvent
extends SailPointObject
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable
    Class used for the audit log of internal system events.

    Actions are extensible and defined in the AuditConfig. Some name constants are defined here for use in system code.

      • getSource

        public java.lang.String getSource()
        Who did it. This will usually be an Identity name, but it can also be used for anonymous events, or events performed by the "system". Note that there is not a direct reference to an Identity object, in part because there is not always an Identity for the event but also because it is undesirable for a foreign key constraint from the audit log which can live forever to an Identity which an be deleted.

      • checkLimits

        public void checkLimits()
        Called immediately prior to storage to make sure the fields are all within the allowed size. Note that if this is called after an existing AuditEvent is fetched, it could cause it to be marked dirty in Hibernate so you should only call this if you are creating a new event, or deliberately modifying an existing one.
